name: intro_group
label: Welcome to Precision Sustainable Agriculture Data Collection form for Cover Crop Biomass Harvest and Decomposition Bags.

name: form_name
label: Form Name

name: form_version
label: Version

name: hotline
label: If you have a problem or need assistance with this protocol you can call our PSA On-Farm Hotline: (919) 410-7841

name: biomass_only
label: Will you be doing the full Decomp Bag protocol or Biomass Only?

name: materials_list_biomass_only
label: Materials Needed: 1) Bags pre-weighed with barcodes - see the Kobo Form "psa bag pre wt" for more information first.  2) hand shears or cutting tools 3) meter sticks 4) PPE

name: materials_list_decomp_bags
label: Materials Needed: 1) Decomp Bags pre-weighed with barcodes - see the Kobo Form "bag pre wt" for more information first. 2) XL plastic bags for biomass harvest 3) hand shears or cutting tools 4) meter sticks 5) field scale to at least 1 decimal point 6) large plastic tub 7) small plastic tub 8) gloves 9) PPE 10) glyphosate and pre-emergents in a spray backpack 11) landscape staples and flags

name: scale_accuracy_note
label: Scale Reminder:  Bring a scale that weighs in grams. +/- 0.1g. Accuracy to  at least one decimal place, use the same scale, or very similar accuracy that you will use for the fresh weight and dry weight of the same bag later on in the process.

name: first_time
label: Is this your first time collecting biomass on-farm for PSA?

name: instructions_group
label: Biomass Instructions

name: url
label: PSA Instructional Video for Collecting Biomass with Kobo Collect

name: url2
label: PSA Protocol for Biomass and Decomp Bags
hint: access through the Google Drive

name: scale_pic
label: First time weighing decomp bags in the field? Here's a sample scale setup with windblock.

name: safetynote
label: SAFTEY: Communicate with the grower about when and which pesticides were used. Use proper re-entry periods and safe handling methods when harvesting biomass with herbicides.  Always use gloves when handling biomass treated with herbicides, and evaluate whether you can use safe grinding procedures when processing biomass later.

name: code
label: What is the 3 letter site Code?

name: termination_date
label: Record the termination date of the cover crop by the farmer
hint: Biomass harvest should be +/- 3 to 4 days around termination

name: group_cc_growth_species
label: Cover Crop Species

name: which_species
label: Which of the following do you have in your cover crop?
hint: select all that apply

name: growth_stage_grains
label: What is the growth stage of your grains?
hint: Ignore if not relevant

name: growth_stage_legumes
label: What is the growth stage of your legumes?
hint: Ignore if not relevant

name: growth_stage_brassicas
label: What is the growth stage of your brassicas?
hint: Ignore if not relevant

name: biomass_diagram
label: Inside each cover crop rep you will take 2 biomass samples - represented here in the diagram as A and B. Each will be 1 meter square area.

name: measure_group
label: Measuring 1 meter

name: drilled_broad
label: Was the cover crop planted with a drill or broadcast?

name: drill_spacing
label: If drilled, what is the drill line spacing in inches?

name: drill_spacing_note
label: That is ${drill_spacing_cm} in centimeters.

name: harvest_length_note
label: To equal 1 meter square area in THIS field - You will harvest:

name: 6_drill_lines
label: 6 drill lines

name: harvest_length_cm
label: ${harvest_length} centimeters each

name: broadcast_note
label: Your field is Broadcast:  You will harvest  full meter square areas (100 cm x 100 cm) by using meter sticks, or a pre-made 1 meter quadrat.
hint: If you choose to do a half meter quadrat, make sure to do it twice for A and twice for B.

label: Begin Rep 1

name: rep_1_start
label: Take 2 large bags, a meter square measuring device, and cutting tools to Rep 1 to harvest A and B

name: biomass_mix_diagram
label: Fresh Material from A and B are combined to make all 12 decomp bags for each rep

name: start_weights_note
label: Start Fresh Weights - Rep 1

name: fresh_wt_group
label: Fresh Weights - In Grams

name: fresh_wt_a1
label: What is the Fresh Wt of Subsample A (fresh biomass/ m2 including the bag) in grams?
hint: We will weigh the bag later

name: fresh_wt_b1
label: What is the Fresh Wt of Subsample B (fresh biomass/ m2 including the bag) in grams?
hint: We will weigh the bag later

name: note_pour_sub1
label: Next pour the contents of both Subsample A and B into one large container or tote. There are 2 meters inside.  Mix them all together.  Walk back into the field, and clip extra handfuls of cover crop and throw them into the tote too.

name: empty_bag_group
label: Empty Bag Weights- In Grams

name: bag_a1
label: What is the weight of empty bag A (in grams)?

name: bag_b1
label: What is the weight of empty bag B (in grams)?

name: calc_group
label: Calculating Decomp Bag Target Fresh Weights - Rep 1

name: average1
label: This is the average fresh weight of 1 meter of biomass in Rep 1 is:

name: sub1_av_note
label: ${sub1_average_fresh_wt}  grams

name: target
label: Next we divide that weight by 6, to get the target fresh weight for each of the 12 decomp bags. Your target fresh weight to stuff inside the decomp bag in Rep 1 is:

name: Target_weight_target1_bag_wt
label: ${target1_bag_wt} grams

name: fillnote1
label: Now fill 12 bags (10 mesh and 2 paper) for rep 1 (A’s and B’s) T0 to T5. Fill them in random order.

name: manual_type_barcode_bag_000

label: You have finished with Rep 2. Return paper bags back to the lab to dry at 60C. The 20 remaining mesh decomp bags (10 from rep 1 and 10 from rep 2) should be placed at the field edge until crop rows are in place.
You have finished with Biomass Harvest for PSA On-Farm

name: biomass_only_end
label: Return 4 bags of fresh biomass to a dryer at 60C. Record the dry weights of the bags in the Kobo form 'psa bag dry wt'.

name: arangement_note
label: When the crop is planted the remaining mesh bags will look like this inside the rows. You will place them at sensor installation.

name: analysis_instructions
label: All samples, the time zero you bring back today and the decomp bags you will leave in the field, will go for analysis. Please dry and grind your Time 0 paper bags ASAP and send a subsample (10 grams of a mix of A and B per rep) them to UGA (using the provided shipping labels and submission form).

name: sub1_legume
label: Is the cover crop in Rep 1 made up of more or less than 40% legume? - Note this for the NIR submission form

name: sub2_legume
label: Is the cover crop in Rep 2 made up of more or less than 40% legume?  - Note this for the NIR submission form

name: more_instructions
label: Now you can proceed to GPS the corners of each treatment and rep using the 'psa gps' form.

name: comments_issues
label: Do you have any comments or issues to report about Biomass Harvest in this field?

name: save_form_name
label: Save the form with the Farm Code so that you may refer to it for NIR submission, and submit the saved form when you return to WiFi
